(40, 15, 29, 43, 6, 1, 1, 'sea of Galilee', 'Jesus and the Sea of Galilee', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' movement towards the sea of Galilee in both passages. Both verses emphasize Jesus'' presence in the region, indicating a continuity in His ministry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 29, 6, 12, 3, 3, 'sea of Galilee', 'Geographical Connection to Galilee', 'Both passages emphasize geographical locations near bodies of water. Matthew mentions the sea of Galilee, while Joshua references the sea of Chinneroth, which is another name for the same body of water.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 29, 23, 9, 1, 1, 'the sea of Galilee', 'Connection between Jesus and Galilee', 'This connection highlights the geographical significance of Galilee in both passages. Jesus'' presence near the sea of Galilee in Matthew reflects the prophetic mention of Galilee in Isaiah, emphasizing its importance in the narrative of affliction and hope.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 29, 41, 1, 16, 16, 'sea of Galilee', 'Connection at the Sea of Galilee', 'Both passages emphasize the Sea of Galilee as a significant location in Jesus'' ministry. In Matthew, Jesus approaches the sea, while in Mark, he interacts with fishermen by the same sea.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 29, 41, 7, 31, 37, 'sea of Galilee', 'Healing and Authority of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' actions near the sea of Galilee, showcasing his authority in healing. The healing of the deaf man in Mark follows his arrival at the sea, illustrating the continuity of his ministry in this region.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 30, 42, 6, 17, 19, 'great multitudes came unto him', 'Healing of the Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of those with various ailments. They describe great multitudes coming to Jesus to be healed, highlighting his miraculous power over diseases and unclean spirits.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 30, 44, 5, 15, 16, 'healed them', 'Healing Miracles of Jesus and Peter', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of the sick and afflicted. In Matthew, Jesus heals those brought to him, while in Acts, Peter''s shadow brings healing to the sick. This connection highlights the continuation of miraculous healing in the early church.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 30, 40, 14, 35, 36, NULL, 'Healing of the Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of those who are diseased or afflicted. In Matthew 15:30, Jesus heals many who are lame, blind, and dumb, while in Matthew 14:35-36, people seek healing by touching his garment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 30, 23, 35, 5, 6, 'those that were lame, blind, dumb', 'Healing and Restoration Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the healing of the blind, lame, and dumb, showcasing a theme of restoration. Matthew 15:30''s healing acts reflect the prophetic vision of Isaiah 35:5-6, where the blind and lame are restored.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 30, 44, 19, 11, 12, 'he healed them', 'Healing Miracles in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize miraculous healings performed by God''s servants. In Matthew, Jesus heals the afflicted, while in Acts, Paul performs miracles that heal the sick.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 30, 19, 103, 3, 3, NULL, 'Healing and Forgiveness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of healing, with Matthew 15:30 depicting Jesus healing various ailments and Psalms 103:3 stating that God heals all diseases. This connection highlights the holistic nature of divine healing, encompassing both physical and spiritual restoration.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 30, 40, 11, 4, 5, NULL, 'Healing Miracles of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' healing of the blind and lame. Matthew 15:30 describes Jesus healing those who were brought to him, while Matthew 11:4-5 lists similar miracles as evidence of his ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 31, 40, 9, 8, 8, NULL, 'Miraculous Acts and Praise', 'Both passages emphasize the response of the multitude to miraculous healings, leading them to glorify God. The acts of healing in Matthew 15:31 and the acknowledgment of God''s power in Matthew 9:8 connect the themes of divine intervention and communal worship.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 31, 42, 18, 43, 43, 'glorified the God of Israel', 'Healing and Praise to God', 'Both passages emphasize miraculous healings that lead to glorifying God. In Matthew, the multitude glorifies God after witnessing various healings, while in Luke, the healed man follows Jesus and praises God, prompting others to do the same.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 31, 1, 32, 28, 28, 'the maimed to be whole', 'Healing and Transformation', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation through divine power. In Matthew, the multitude witnesses miraculous healings, while in Genesis, Jacob''s name change signifies a new identity and strength with God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 31, 19, 50, 15, 15, 'glorified the God of Israel', 'Glorifying God in Deliverance', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God following deliverance from affliction. In Matthew, the multitude glorifies God after witnessing miraculous healings, while in Psalms, the promise of deliverance is linked to glorifying God in times of trouble.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 31, 19, 50, 23, 23, 'glorified the God of Israel', 'Praise and Glorification of God', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God in response to miraculous works and righteous living. The multitude in Matthew glorifies God after witnessing healing, while Psalms connects glorification with offering praise and living rightly.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 31, 40, 9, 33, 33, 'the dumb to speak', 'Miraculous Healings and Marvel', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous healings performed by Jesus, leading to wonder among the multitudes. The response of the people in both instances highlights their amazement and glorification of God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 31, 42, 7, 16, 16, 'glorified the God of Israel', 'Glorifying God for Miracles', 'Both passages emphasize the response of the people to miraculous events, leading them to glorify God. In Matthew, the multitude glorifies the God of Israel after witnessing healings, while in Luke, the people glorify God after recognizing a great prophet among them.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 32, 40, 9, 36, 36, 'compassion on the multitude', 'Compassion for the Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' compassion for the crowds. In Matthew 15:32, he expresses concern for their physical needs, while in Matthew 9:36, he is moved by their spiritual condition, describing them as faint and scattered.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 32, 42, 12, 29, 30, 'nothing to eat', 'Compassion and Provision', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s provision for physical needs. Both passages emphasize the importance of not worrying about food, as God is aware of these needs.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 32, 44, 27, 33, 33, NULL, 'Compassion and Fasting', 'This connection highlights the theme of compassion for those who are fasting and in need of sustenance. Both passages emphasize the importance of providing food for those who have been without it for an extended period.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 32, 40, 14, 14, 21, 'I have compassion on the multitude', 'Compassion and Feeding the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' compassion for the multitude and his miraculous provision of food. In Matthew 15:32, Jesus expresses concern for the crowd''s hunger, paralleling his earlier act of feeding in Matthew 14:14-21, where he also shows compassion and provides sustenance.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 32, 41, 8, 1, 10, 'I have compassion on the multitude', 'Compassion for the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' compassion for the multitude who have been with him for three days without food. This shared theme highlights his concern for their well-being and the need to provide for them before sending them away.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 32, 9, 30, 11, 12, 'three days', 'Compassion for the Hungry', 'This connection highlights the theme of compassion for those in need of food. Both passages depict individuals who have gone without sustenance for three days, emphasizing the urgency of providing nourishment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 32, 41, 9, 22, 22, 'compassion', 'Compassion in Times of Need', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of compassion in moments of distress. In Matthew, Jesus shows compassion for the hungry multitude, while in Mark, the plea for help highlights the need for compassion in suffering.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 15, 33, 40, 14, 15, 15, NULL, 'Disciples'' Concern for Food', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' concern about feeding a large crowd in a desert place. In Matthew 15:33, they question the availability of bread, while in Matthew 14:15, they suggest sending the multitude away to buy food.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
